
I light a cigarette
I outline your cocaine sillohete
We share a smoker's kiss
And fall into an eternal bliss
You smoke a cigarette
You are my heroine marionette
We share a poisonous kiss
And fall into an endless rehab abyss
I put out a cigarette
And light another with no regret
We share a nicotine filled kiss
And we, addicts, sit there and wish